Tropical storm Floyd was predicted to intensify, likely sparing the Caribbean islands but posing a potential threat to the Bahamas.
Residents in Anguilla prepared for the worst, while Floridians stocked up on supplies.
Forecasters warned of the storm's rapid strengthening, with the possibility of a hurricane watch for eastern Florida.
NASA planned to close the Kennedy Space Center as a precaution.
FEMA officials assured a swift response regardless of where Floyd made landfall, emphasizing the importance of preparedness.
Evacuations were underway in vulnerable coastal areas, with concerns about destructive winds and storm surges.
